The LSP states that "objects in a program should be replaceable with instances of their subtypes without altering the correctness of the program." This means that we should be able to use a subclass object where a superclass object is expected without any issues. However, in this case, the `Cube` class violates the LSP because it has a different implementation for the `calculate_area()` method than its parent class `Shape`.

